   "source": [
    "# Emotion Classification with Attention 🎭\n",
    "\n",
    "**Multi-class emotion classification (joy, sadness, anger, fear, surprise, disgust) using sequence models with attention, built on Google's GoEmotions dataset.**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook covers the full project pipeline:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Load & explore the real **GoEmotions** dataset (Google Research)\n",
    "2. Map the 27 fine-grained GoEmotions labels → **6 core (Ekman) emotion classes**\n",
    "3. Clean, tokenize, and pad text\n",
    "4. Build an embedding layer initialized with pretrained **GloVe** vectors\n",
    "5. Build and compare **four architectures**: LSTM, GRU, BiLSTM + Attention, and a fine-tuned **DistilBERT** (HuggingFace `Trainer`)\n",
    "6. Evaluate with accuracy, macro F1, per-class precision/recall, and confusion matrices\n",
    "7. Visualize **attention heatmaps** to interpret predictions token-by-token\n",
    "8. Save the trained model + tokenizer for the companion **Streamlit** app\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Data source:** this notebook downloads the *exact* official GoEmotions train/dev/test splits directly from Google's `google-research` GitHub repository — no manual download needed.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
