    "## 1. Load the GoEmotions Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "[GoEmotions](https://github.com/google-research/google-research/tree/master/goemotions) (Demszky et al., 2020, Google Research) is a corpus of **58k carefully curated Reddit comments**, human-annotated with **27 fine-grained emotions + neutral**.\n",
    "\n",
    "We use the **official, rater-agreement-filtered train/dev/test split** (`train.tsv` / `dev.tsv` / `test.tsv`) shipped in the `google-research/google-research` GitHub repo, along with:\n",
    "- `emotions.txt` — the ordered list of the 28 label names\n",
    "- `ekman_mapping.json` — Google's own mapping from the 27 fine-grained emotions to **Paul Ekman's 6 basic emotions** (anger, disgust, fear, joy, sadness, surprise)\n",
    "\n",
    "We download these files directly so the notebook always uses the *exact* same source data."
   ]
  },
