   "source": [
    "## 3. Mapping GoEmotions → 6 Core Emotion Classes\n",
    "\n",
    "GoEmotions is **multi-label** and has 27 fine-grained categories + neutral. To get clean single-label targets for our 6 classes (**joy, sadness, anger, fear, surprise, disgust**), we use Google's official `ekman_mapping.json` and the following rule for every comment:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Map every fine-grained label present on the comment to its Ekman category (drop `neutral`, which has no Ekman category).\n",
    "2. **Keep** the comment only if all of its labels map to **exactly one** Ekman category → that becomes the single target class.\n",
    "3. **Drop** the comment if it is neutral-only, or if its labels span **more than one** Ekman category (genuinely ambiguous / mixed-emotion comments).\n",
    "\n",
    "This keeps the task a clean single-label 6-way classification problem while staying faithful to GoEmotions' own annotation scheme."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "037c449b",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-07-21T23:59:51.543786Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-07-21T23:59:51.543570Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-07-21T23:59:51.616059Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-07-21T23:59:51.614970Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Target classes: ['anger', 'disgust', 'fear', 'joy', 'sadness', 'surprise']\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "train: kept  28104 /  43410  (64.7%)\n",
      "  dev: kept   3527 /   5426  (65.0%)\n",
      " test: kept   3539 /   5427  (65.2%)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ekman_map = json.load(open(\"data/ekman_mapping.json\"))\n",
    "EMOTION_CLASSES = sorted(ekman_map.keys())  # anger, disgust, fear, joy, sadness, surprise\n",
    "print(\"Target classes:\", EMOTION_CLASSES)\n",
    "\n",
    "fine_to_ekman = {fine: cat for cat, fines in ekman_map.items() for fine in fines}\n",
    "\n",
    "def map_row_to_ekman(label_ids_str):\n",
    "    ids = [int(x) for x in label_ids_str.split(\",\")]\n",
    "    names = [emotions[i] for i in ids]\n",
    "    cats = {fine_to_ekman[n] for n in names if n in fine_to_ekman}  # 'neutral' -> not in dict -> dropped\n",
    "    return list(cats)[0] if len(cats) == 1 else None\n",
    "\n",
    "def prep_split(df):\n",
    "    df = df.copy()\n",
    "    df[\"emotion\"] = df[\"label_ids\"].apply(map_row_to_ekman)\n",
    "    kept = df.dropna(subset=[\"emotion\"]).reset_index(drop=True)\n",
    "    return kept\n",
    "\n",
    "train_df = prep_split(raw_train)\n",
    "val_df   = prep_split(raw_dev)\n",
    "test_df  = prep_split(raw_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "for name, before, after in [(\"train\", raw_train, train_df), (\"dev\", raw_dev, val_df), (\"test\", raw_test, test_df)]:\n",
    "    print(f\"{name:>5s}: kept {len(after):>6d} / {len(before):>6d}  ({len(after)/len(before)*100:.1f}%)\")\n"
   ]
  },
